{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So it turns out that mathematics is a very powerful language."},{"time":3671,"text":"It has generated considerable insight in physics,"},{"time":5983,"text":"in biology and economics,"},{"time":8083,"text":"but not that much in the humanities and in history."},{"time":10900,"text":"I think there's a belief that it's just impossible,"},{"time":13183,"text":"that you cannot quantify the doings of mankind,"},{"time":15829,"text":"that you cannot measure history."},{"time":18348,"text":"But I don't think that's right."},{"time":19875,"text":"I want to show you a couple of examples why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21917,"text":"So my collaborator Erez and I were considering the following fact:"},{"time":24875,"text":"that two kings separated by centuries"},{"time":27604,"text":"will speak a very different language."},{"time":29371,"text":"That's a powerful historical force."},{"time":31675,"text":"So the king of England, Alfred the Great,"},{"time":33448,"text":"will use a vocabulary and grammar"},{"time":35088,"text":"that is quite different from the king of hip hop, Jay-Z."},{"time":38788,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":40454,"text":"Now it's just the way it is."},{"time":42625,"text":"Language changes over time, and it's a powerful force."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44917,"text":"So Erez and I wanted to know more about that."},{"time":47204,"text":"So we paid attention to a particular grammatical rule, past-tense conjugation."},{"time":50861,"text":"So you just add \"ed\" to a verb at the end to signify the past."},{"time":54125,"text":"\"Today I walk. Yesterday I walked.\""},{"time":56052,"text":"But some verbs are irregular."},{"time":57396,"text":"\"Yesterday I thought.\""},{"time":58792,"text":"Now what's interesting about that"},{"time":60458,"text":"is irregular verbs between Alfred and Jay-Z have become more regular."},{"time":64288,"text":"Like the verb \"to wed\" that you see here has become regular."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67023,"text":"So Erez and I followed the fate of over 100 irregular verbs"},{"time":71045,"text":"through 12 centuries of English language,"},{"time":72964,"text":"and we saw that there's actually a very simple mathematical pattern"},{"time":75875,"text":"that captures this complex historical change,"},{"time":78417,"text":"namely, if a verb is 100 times more frequent than another,"},{"time":82077,"text":"it regularizes 10 times slower."},{"time":84742,"text":"That's a piece of history, but it comes in a mathematical wrapping."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88677,"text":"Now in some cases math can even help explain,"},{"time":92331,"text":"or propose explanations for, historical forces."},{"time":95210,"text":"So here Steve Pinker and I"},{"time":97042,"text":"were considering the magnitude of wars during the last two centuries."},{"time":100894,"text":"There's actually a well-known regularity to them"},{"time":103389,"text":"where the number of wars that are 100 times deadlier"},{"time":106811,"text":"is 10 times smaller."},{"time":108763,"text":"So there are 30 wars that are about as deadly as the Six Days War,"},{"time":112107,"text":"but there's only four wars that are 100 times deadlier --"},{"time":114927,"text":"like World War I."},{"time":116904,"text":"So what kind of historical mechanism can produce that?"},{"time":119827,"text":"What's the origin of this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":121827,"text":"So Steve and I, through mathematical analysis,"},{"time":124092,"text":"propose that there's actually a very simple phenomenon at the root of this,"},{"time":128333,"text":"which lies in our brains."},{"time":130023,"text":"This is a very well-known feature"},{"time":132042,"text":"in which we perceive quantities in relative ways --"},{"time":135017,"text":"quantities like the intensity of light or the loudness of a sound."},{"time":138733,"text":"For instance, committing 10,000 soldiers to the next battle sounds like a lot."},{"time":144042,"text":"It's relatively enormous if you've already committed 1,000 soldiers previously."},{"time":147486,"text":"But it doesn't sound so much,"},{"time":149313,"text":"it's not relatively enough, it won't make a difference"},{"time":152333,"text":"if you've already committed 100,000 soldiers previously."},{"time":155285,"text":"So you see that because of the way we perceive quantities,"},{"time":158898,"text":"as the war drags on,"},{"time":160665,"text":"the number of soldiers committed to it and the casualties"},{"time":163750,"text":"will increase not linearly --"},{"time":165433,"text":"like 10,000, 11,000, 12,000 --"},{"time":167321,"text":"but exponentially -- 10,000, later 20,000, later 40,000."},{"time":171596,"text":"And so that explains this pattern that we've seen before."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174681,"text":"So here mathematics is able to link a well-known feature of the individual mind"},{"time":180179,"text":"with a long-term historical pattern"},{"time":183168,"text":"that unfolds over centuries and across continents."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186025,"text":"So these types of examples, today there are just a few of them,"},{"time":190042,"text":"but I think in the next decade they will become commonplace."},{"time":192731,"text":"The reason for that is that the historical record"},{"time":195123,"text":"is becoming digitized at a very fast pace."},{"time":197583,"text":"So there's about 130 million books"},{"time":200193,"text":"that have been written since the dawn of time."},{"time":202504,"text":"Companies like Google have digitized many of them --"},{"time":204958,"text":"above 20 million actually."},{"time":206542,"text":"And when the stuff of history is available in digital form,"},{"time":210120,"text":"it makes it possible for a mathematical analysis"},{"time":212500,"text":"to very quickly and very conveniently"},{"time":214875,"text":"review trends in our history and our culture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217600,"text":"So I think in the next decade,"},{"time":220321,"text":"the sciences and the humanities will come closer together"},{"time":223071,"text":"to be able to answer deep questions about mankind."},{"time":226400,"text":"And I think that mathematics will be a very powerful language to do that."},{"time":230521,"text":"It will be able to reveal new trends in our history,"},{"time":233667,"text":"sometimes to explain them,"},{"time":235417,"text":"and maybe even in the future to predict what's going to happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238723,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240214,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}